col.name: alt_sample_name
description: if another identifier is used, for example in supplemental tables

col.name: unique_patient_ID
description: Use this column if there are technical replicates.  If this column contains non-unique entries-- expression values of those arrays will eventually be averaged.

col.name: sample_type
description: healthy should be only from individuals without cancer| adjacentnormal from individuals with cancer| metastatic for non-primary distant tumors

col.name: histology
description: sq = squamous; la = lung adenocarcinoma ?; ad = adenocarcinoma; nsclc_squa = non-small cell lung cancer squamous; nsclc_nos = non-small cell lung carcinoma not otherwise specified; nsclc_adeno = non-small cell lung cancer adenocarcinoma;lcuc = large cell undifferentiated carcinoma; ctr_infl = ??? (only in GSE11117, not sure what it refers to...)

col.name: T
description: describes the size of the tumor and wehther it has invaded nearby tissue

col.name: pstage
description: describes the size of the tumor and wehther it has invaded nearby tissue.  NOTE: Some studies have T and pstage and the values are different, so we've included both for comprehensiveness

col.name: N
description: descibes regional lymph nodes that are involved (0 = tumor cells absent from regional lymph nodes; 1 = regional lymph node metastasis present)

col.name: substage
description: substage (abcd).  For cases like ab, bc-- use highest given

col.name: egfr_status
description: epidermal growth factor receptor wildtype or mutant

col.name: gefitinib_treatment
description: Gefitinib is an EGFR inhibitor and is only effective in cancers with mutated and overactive EGFR

col.name: summary_grade
description: moderately = G2 (intermediate grade); poorly = G3 (High grade); well = G1 (low grade)

col.name: days_to_tumor_recurrence
description: time to recurrence or last follow-up in days

col.name: days_to_death
description: time to death or last follow-up in days
